1. Možemo da se oslonimo jedni na druge, jer imamo *poverenja*. (We can rely on each other, because we have trust.)
2. Molim te, *poveri* mi ovaj zadatak. (Please entrust me with this task.)
3. Kompanija je pretrpela veliku štetu nakon što je izgubila *poverenje* javnosti. (The company suffered a great damage after losing public trust.)
4. *Poverenik* za zaštitu podataka o ličnosti je nezavisan organ koji štiti privatnost građana. (The Commissioner for Information of Public Importance and Personal Data Protection is an independent authority that protects citizens' privacy.)
5. Moramo da uspostavimo *poverenje* sa novim klijentima kako bismo uspeli da ostvarimo posao. (We need to establish trust with new clients in order to succeed in business.)
6. Taj slučaj je tajna, molim te, drži to u *poverenju*. (That case is confidential, please keep it in confidence.)
7. Ukoliko želimo da imamo uspešan odnos, *poverenje* je ključno. (If we want to have a successful relationship, trust is crucial.)
8. Potrebno je da *poverimo* ove dokumente advokatu koji će ih pregledati. (We need to entrust these documents to the lawyer who will review them.)
9. Kao novi direktor, moraću da se izborim za *poverenje* zaposlenih. (As a new director, I will have to earn the trust of the employees.)
10. Prijatelji se međusobno podržavaju i imaju *poverenje* jedni u druge. (Friends support each other and have trust in each other.)